 {
  "id": "county-id-coverage-note",
  "person": "(coverage)",
  "role": "Idaho sheriffs \u2014 coverage note",
  "jurisdiction": "Idaho",
  "branch": "law_enforcement",
  "level": "county",
  "status": "incumbent",
  "party": "",
  "as_of": "2026-07-04",
  "source_url": "https://www.idahosheriffs.org/",
  "source_dataset": "county_sheriffs",
  "note": "All 44/44 counties returned via the Idaho Sheriffs' Association 'Meet the Sheriffs' directory. Web-verified a representative sample against county/official/news sources: Ada (Clifford), Canyon (Donahue), Kootenai (Norris), Twin Falls (Johnson), Bonneville (Hulse), Latah (Skiles), Nez Perce (Scrimsher), Blaine (Ballis), plus ISA officers Butte (Hansen, 2026 pres.), Bannock (Manu), Adams (Zollman). Turnover: the ISA directory still lists Shoshone as 'Vacant', but the current sheriff is Shawn Wehr, a mid-term appointee sworn in 2026-03-27 (after Lindsey resigned Oct 2025, Eddy appointed Nov 2025 then resigned Feb 2026). Genuinely new via Nov 2024 election, seated 2025-01-13: Twin Falls (Johnson) and Blaine (Ballis). Party filled (all Republican) only where directly evidenced: 11 verified Republican; remaining 33 left blank per evidence rule (Idaho sheriffs are partisan-elected 4-yr terms and the state is overwhelmingly Republican, but individual party affiliation was not independently confirmed for those). No Democratic-affiliated sheriff was confirmed. Most recent general election Nov 2024, seated Jan 2025."
 }
